com.misc.common.moplaf.propagator2

Interface PropagatorFunction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    PropagatorFunctionBindings
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PropagatorFunctionBindingsImpl, PropagatorFunctionImpl

    public interface PropagatorFunction
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'PropagatorFunction'.

    Manage the refresh of derived data elements. The PropagatorFunction declares other PropagatorFunctions it depends (doGetAntecedents() and doGetParent()), remembers whether out of date, and ultimately calls methods doRefresh() or doRefresh(EObject) when the derived elements must be recalculated.

    Listening to changes is delegated to a PropagatorFunctionSource that is attached to the adapter PropagatorFunctionAdapter of the targetted object EObject.

    A PropagatorFunction:

    • offers two call-backs methods that may be overridden by the concrete PropagatorFunction in order to implement the refresh logic for the derived elements this adapter is responsible for; the whole purpose of the present framework is to call one of these methods exactly when needed:
      • doRefresh(), that will be called when no touching EObject has been tracked
      • doRefresh(EObject), that will be called for every touching EObject that has been tracked, if any
    • maintains its touched state
      • whether this PropagatorFunction is up to date or not: method isTouched()
        • touched = not proven up to date with respect to its direct antecedents = needs refresh
        • not touched = up to date with respects to its direct antecedents
      • a collection of touched children of this PropagatorFunction: method getTouchedChildren()
      • a collection of Notifier's responsible for the touching: method getTouchers()
    • offers a method, insuring that this Propagator become up to date: method refresh(); this entails
      • refreshing all antecedents ancestors: the parent, the parent's parent, ..., recursively
      • refreshing all antecedents siblings, antecedent's antecedents sibling, ... recursively
      • refreshing all children
      • refreshing this PropagatorFunction: method doRefresh()
    • declares
      • a Parent PropagatorFunction: method getParent()
      • a collection PropagatorFunction on which this PropagatorFunction depends: the Antecedents: method getAntecedents()
      satisfying
      • first the antecedents siblings will be refreshed
      • second the children will be refreshed
      • finally this PropagatorFunction will be refreshed
    • offers the following methods, to be implemented by the concrete class
      • method doGetParent()
      • method doGetAntecedents()
      • method doRefresh()
      that are used by this PropagatorFunction for deriving the following data
      • the Parent of this PropagatorFunction
      • the Antecedents of this PropagatorFunction
      • the AntecedentsSibling of this PropagatorFunction
      • to refresh the derived data this ProgatorFunction is responsible for

    The PropagatorFunction life cycle is as follows

    • The life cycle is controlled by a PropagatorFunctionManagerAdapter which is responsible for creating, enabling and disabling the PropagatorFunction
    • The construction of the PropagatorFunction is implemented in a PropagatorFunctionsConstructor, which is responsible, for every type ObjectWithPropagatorFunctions to create the appropriate PropagatorFunctions and to add them by calling the method ObjectWithPropagatorFunctions.addPropagatorFunction(PropagatorFunction)
    • the construction is done when the object is contained, called by the method PropagatorFunctionManagerAdapter#onNotifierContained)
    • It is enabled when the PropagatorFunctionManagerAdapter is added to the scope of the propagation (method enable(), called by PropagatorFunctionManagerAdapter.onAdapterAdded(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier))
    • It is disabled when the PropagatorFunctionManagerAdapter is removed from the scope of the propagation(method disable(), called by PropagatorFunctionManagerAdapter.onAdapterRemoved(org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier))
    • The Parent of the a PropagatorFunction is supposed to be available when the propagator is enabled (typically when the propagator is owned), and is supposed never change. Touches are lost with ownership.
    Author:
    michel

    The following features are supported:

    • Parent
    • Antecedents
    • Antecedents Sibling
    • Touched
    • Touched Children
    • Touchers
    • Enabled
    • Object With Propagator Functions
